In economics and finance, '''in kind''' refers to goods, services, and transactions not involving [[money]] or not measured in monetary terms. For example: *[[Payment in kind (disambiguation)|Payment in kind]], or [[barter]]: exchange of goods or services for other goods or services with no [[medium of exchange]] *[[Income in kind]]: in particular **[[Benefit in kind]]: employee benefits such as a [[company car]] or gym membership *[[Tax in kind]]: such as a [[tithe]] from farmer's crops *[[Calculation in kind]]: a type of accounting based on physical magnitudes and physical quantities rather than a common [[unit of account]] *[[Gifts in kind]]: charitable donation of goods or services, as opposed to donation of money to buy goods and services
